text: Los Angeles, the largest metropolitan area in California, joined much of the state Sunday afternoon in announcing coronavirus restrictions, including at least a three-week prohibition on dining out at restaurants. https://t.co/8ZXxy2uAYH

name: sfchronicle
text:
Weary of months of lockdown and isolation, many people are flying in or out of the Bay Area to see family over Thanksgiving even as officials have begged Americans not to travel for the holiday.

Story by @TatianaYSanchez: https://t.co/ybg0xG82yF

text:

President-elect Joe Biden is expected to nominate Antony Blinken as secretary of state, according to multiple people familiar with the Biden team's planning.

name: sfchronicle
text:
San Francisco on Sunday again avoided being banished to the state’s most restrictive purple tier, even as as coronavirus cases surged. But residents shouldn't get their hopes up: It’s still likely to happen this week, officials said.

Story by @SFJKDineen: https://t.co/vu2sT41xvb

name: sfchronicle
text:
BREAKING: California Gov. Gavin Newsom and his family in quarantine after virus exposure.

Story by @KateGalbraith: https://t.co/QoTIv4Kj4X

name: sfchronicle
text:
BREAKING: Two people were killed and multiple people were stabbed at the Grace Baptist Church near San Jose State University Sunday night, San Jose police said.

Story by @pfimrite: https://t.co/ekCIaKX2rY

name: sfchronicle
text: @pfimrite Police rushed to the scene at the church, at 484 East San Fernando St., shortly after 9 p.m. Sunday and found multiple victims, the police tweeted over their media relations channel. https://t.co/FlZ36NTDUy

name: sfchronicle
text: “For clarification, no church services were being conducted at the time of the stabbing.” police said. “Unhoused individuals were brought into the church to get them out of the cold.” https://t.co/FlZ36NTDUy

name: sfchronicle
text: @KateGalbraith “Late Friday evening, @JenSiebelNewsom and I learned that 3 of our children had been exposed to an officer from the California Highway Patrol who had tested positive for COVID-19,” Newsom tweeted Sunday. https://t.co/SrbvKFavn0

name: sfchronicle
text: @KateGalbraith A Newsom spokesperson said Newsom and Siebel Newsom “had no direct interaction with the officer. The family were all tested today and are all negative for COVID-19. However, consistent with local guidance, the family has begun to quarantine.” https://t.co/SrbvKFavn0
